Supporting Materials for the Review of EGB Haddock

Tom Carruthers tom@bluematterscience.com

11 March, 2022

 

 

Software

 

Wood’s Hole Assessment Model (WHAM)

For more information about WHAM you can go to the WHAM homepage

or read the peer-reviewed paper by Stock and Miller 2021

 

OpenMSE

For more information about the OpenMSE software (Hordyk et al.) used in reference point calculation, projection and plan-B testing visit the openMSE homepage.

The operating model equations are identical to those detailed in the appendices of the peer-reviewed paper for DLMtool Carruthers & Hordyk 2019

   

R Code

R code for TOR 4 (Assessment), TOR 6 (Projection), TOR 8 (Plan - B assessment), TOR 11 (Reference points) is available from a private GitHub repository

Please email tom@bluematterscience or failing that, quang@bluematterscience for access to the repository.

The repo has the following folder structure:

Folder Contents
/Data Raw and processed data used in the fitting of assessments and production of operating models
/Figures TOR 4, 6, 8 and 11 Figures
/Tables TOR 4, 6, 8 and 11 Tables
/TOR 4 i - Standard SCA Specification & fitting of ‘standard’ statistical catch at age WHAM models without time varying M
/TOR 4 ii - Time Varying Survival Specification & fitting of WHAM models including time varying M
/TOR 4 iii - Sim testing Simulation self-testing of time varying M models
/TOR 4 iv - Base EGB model Specification, fitting and generic wham report building for the Base (Mest) assessment model including jitters
/TOR 4 v - Fit Retro Estimates Plotting of fitting diagnostics, M LHF profiling, retrospective diagnostics and model estimates
/TOR 4 vi - Sensitivity Base EGB Specification, fitting & results of sensitivity analyses for the Base (Mest) assessment model
/TOR 6 Projections Projection of Base (Mest) assessment model including TAC alternatives and risk profiles
/TOR 8 - Plan B EGB Closed-loop simulation testing of existing and new management procedures for EGB haddock including plan-B-smooth
/TOR 11 i - Make EGB OM Specification of openMSE operating models for the Base (Mest) assessment for the purposes of reference point calculation, projections and plan-B MP evaluation
/TOR 11 ii - Reference points EGB Code to investigate alternative reference points for EGB haddock including FXSPR ref points
/VPA Code and documentation for the continuity VPA run
/WHAM Additional code and data to support EGB assessment
/Z - Old scripts Disused code for reference

   

Within each folder there are calculation scripts starting a_, b_ etc and then source code, Tabulation and Figure scripts (x_, y_, z_).

To run through the various analyses, first run the Dependencies.R script in the base directory.

The correct order to run through the scripts from scratch is:

  • TOR 4 i-vi (assessment)
  • TOR 11 i & ii (reference points),
  • TOR 6 (projections - uses operating model and reference points from TOR 11)
  • TOR 8 (plan B - uses operating model and reference points from TOR 11)
